comment: * Constants to interact with the blocked numbers list.

variables.name: CONTENT_URI
variables.comment:
* Content URI for the blocked numbers. *

Supported operations

*

blocked *

    *
  • query *
  • delete *
  • insert *
*

blocked/ID *

    *
  • query (selection is not supported) *
  • delete (selection is not supported) *

variables.name: CONTENT_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The MIME type of {@link #CONTENT_URI} itself providing a directory of blocked phone
         * numbers.

variables.name: CONTENT_ITEM_TYPE
variables.comment: * The MIME type of a blocked phone number under {@link #CONTENT_URI}.

variables.name: COLUMN_ID
variables.comment:
* Auto-generated ID field which monotonically increases. *

TYPE: long

variables.name: COLUMN_ORIGINAL_NUMBER
variables.comment:
* Phone number to block. *

Must be specified in {@code insert}. *

TYPE: String

variables.name: COLUMN_E164_NUMBER
variables.comment:
* Phone number to block. The system generates it from {@link #COLUMN_ORIGINAL_NUMBER} * by removing all formatting characters. *

Optional in {@code insert}. When not specified, the system tries to generate it * assuming the current country. (Which will still be null if the number is not valid.) *

TYPE: String
